% ============================================================================
%  references.bib  —  MASTER BIBLIOGRAPHY (single source of truth)
%  Tony Di Fabbio · LINERFUN · https://difabbiot.github.io/
% ============================================================================
%
%  This file drives the publication list on research.html.
%  Regenerate the HTML with:   python3 mybiblio/bib2html.py
%
%  CONVENTIONS (read before editing — bib2html.py relies on them)
%  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
%  1. CITE KEY = HTML ANCHOR.  Entry key `fluids24`  ->  <div class="pub"
%     id="pub-fluids24">.  Keep keys stable: the expertise cards on
%     research.html deep-link to these #pub-... anchors. Renaming a key
%     breaks those links.
%
%  2. ENTRY TYPE -> SECTION.
%        @article                      -> "Journal Articles"
%        @inproceedings / @conference  -> "Conference Papers"
%        @phdthesis / @mastersthesis   -> "Theses"
%     Order inside each section = order in this file (newest first).
%     A conference entry with `presentation = {true}` is routed instead to
%     "Conference Presentations" — a talk given WITHOUT a proceedings paper.
%
%  3. AUTHORS.  Write "Last, F." separated by " and ", e.g.
%        author = {Di Fabbio, T. and Tangermann, E.}
%     bib2html renders "F. Last" and auto-bolds any "Di Fabbio" entry.
%
%  4. VENUE STRING is built automatically:
%        @article  ->  {journal}, {year}[, {volume}({number})]
%        @*proc    ->  {booktitle}, {year}        (put the city IN booktitle)
%        @*thesis  ->  {PhD thesis|Master's thesis} · {school} · {year} · {note}
%
%  5. LINKS (optional, both rendered as buttons under the entry):
%        doi   = {10.xxxx/yyyy}     -> "doi: ..." link to https://doi.org/...
%        oaurl = {https://...}      -> "PDF" button (free/open-access full text)
%        pdf   = {papers/KEY.pdf}   -> "PDF" button to a self-hosted copy
%     PAPER HOSTING: drop self-archived PDFs in mybiblio/papers/ (see the
%     README there). For paywalled papers, host the ACCEPTED MANUSCRIPT
%     (author version, no publisher banner/typesetting) and point `pdf` at it.
%
%  6. `contribution = {...}` is a private CV note. Not rendered by default.
% ============================================================================


